Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.48,0:00:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Dr. David Hawkins Sedona 2002\Nseries, The Way to God. Lecture 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.72,0:00:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception and Illusion: Distortions of\NReality. Originally presented May 11th,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.96,0:00:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,2002 at the Sedona Creative Life Center.\NWell, I'm still on a Walmart high rather
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.36,0:00:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,than Walmart yesterday\Nand uh it's higher than a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,churches in this world. I met a lot of\Nchurches in this world. You go into
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart and everybody sort of drops\Ntheir persona. Everybody just who they
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.84,0:00:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,are like right off the bat. And I\Nnoticed yesterday every single person
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.07,0:00:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,smiled.\NEverybody they pass each other in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.87,0:00:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,baskets and they just smile each other.\NEverybody's just who they are. Holy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.92,0:01:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmarts. Uh,\Neverybody drops their persona and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.55,0:01:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they're just who they are. And uh, of\Ncourse, your willingness to be who you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.68,0:01:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are with them brings it out in them. And\Neverybody's looking at each other's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.28,0:01:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,baskets. What are you having a birthday?\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.84,0:01:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it was really lovely. uh you know in\NParis as far as I did remark about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.04,0:01:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmarts and uh and and Sam and I\Ncorresponded back and forth and he liked
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.47,0:01:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the book and the and you know I was\Nlooking at integrity in business
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.64,0:01:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and we remarked about the integrity of\NWalmarts which in those days calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.68,0:01:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the high 300s well 350 is\Nwillingness, helpfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.47,0:01:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,good-heartedness,\Nuh integrity etc. So I admired his
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.39,0:01:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,putting integrity uh in into the\Nworkplace into business and uh and so we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.52,0:02:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,had sort of a a mutual appreciation and\Nuh and now we see Walmart has become uh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the biggest corporation the biggest\Ncompany in the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.87,0:02:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The W somebody from the Wall Street\NJournal had called me about the validity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.12,0:02:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual concepts in the workplace\Nin business
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.23,0:02:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think Walmart speaks for itself.\NYou calibrated 380 and become the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,biggest corporation in the world.\NOther corporations that calibrate around
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,70 have gone bankrupt.\NSo uh it would it's you know it speaks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for itself the fact that spiritual\Nprinciples as long as you don't call
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.00,0:02:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,them spiritual if you call things God or\Nspiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.16,0:02:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you get a negative reaction from a\Nsegment of the population
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.95,0:03:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but as I say God sneaks in the back door\Nas integrity integrous business
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.48,0:03:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,principles because they show up in the\Nbottom line
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so yesterday the people were saying\Nhow may I help you? I mean wow what a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.44,0:03:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,great space to come from. Who else in\Nthe world comes from how may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.59,0:03:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah the motor vehicle bureau doesn't\Nyou know I mean
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.36,0:03:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,IRS doesn't. Uh so the the world uh\Nthe the government especially you could
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,take a a lesson from Walmart because\Nit's attitude attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,uh being responsible for being uh\Nfriendly and helpful to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.15,0:03:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wasn't going to talk about\NWalmarts this morning, but
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the fifth of a series of 12\Nlectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.76,0:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nthe the design the overall design of the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures is to\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.40,0:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,create uh a field of understanding of\Nthings that are very difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.36,0:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,historically been difficult to\Nunderstand
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and to approach it from the side of the\Nego. So these beginning lectures have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,been designed to familiarize us with the\Nego and how it functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,um how to spot\Nthe fulcrum by which the the ego takes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.56,0:04:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,off in one of two directions to create a\Ndualistic perception of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.19,0:04:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Um and so\Nthe spiritual advancement then is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.80,0:04:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,obstructed by the structures of the ego\Nand therefore we've spent several
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.91,0:04:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures on studying the structure of\Nthe ego which is the title of today's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.32,0:04:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture. What is the title of today's\Nlecture? I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.32,0:04:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Num something about being warped out by
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.88,0:05:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the illusion and\Nperception and illusion and the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.47,0:05:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,distortions of reality.\NSo to fully understand that then we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.16,0:05:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,continue on the lecture series. Um\Ntoday we're going to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,context versus content.\Nhow truth becomes distorted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.36,0:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nit becomes almost an editorial style in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,our in our society\Nin which
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain way of distorting reality\Nbecomes labeled and given a political
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.56,0:05:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,title.\NThose are on the left and there's those
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.72,0:05:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,on the right. You see depends on what\Nkind of a spin. So we recognize that in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.91,0:05:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,common sense we talk about the spin\Ndoctors
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:06:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but just how does that come about and\Nwhat is the impact on society.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So in our writings and our studies uh we\Nlook at society as a collect as as the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.28,0:06:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,collective ego.\NSo looking at the world and looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.52,0:06:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself,\Nit's a lot easier to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.31,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the machinations of the ego\Nuh in the world because we don't feel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,personal personal about it. It's easy to\Nsee it out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.91,0:06:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way of understanding our own ego\Nis to see how it functions in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Society is the big model out there. One\Nreason people love movies is you can sit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.36,0:06:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the safety of your home and without\Ngetting personally involved
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh watch the vagaries of the ego as it\Nworks itself. It's easy to see out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.12,0:06:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there. So if we understand something\Nabout the functions of the ego, its its
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:07:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanisms and its structure\Nand we observe its functioning in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.12,0:07:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,world, it's an easy step then to see\Nthat it's probably going on within
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.63,0:07:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,myself. If it's not going on within\Nmyself, I wouldn't find the world
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.44,0:07:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting.\NIf it's not going in on within myself, I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.19,0:07:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't recognize it in a movie. So we\Ncan say then that the world out there is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a projection of what is within us and\Nstudying the world then gives us an
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.96,0:07:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,indirect\Nit's easier to accept it's easier to see
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,out there\Nthen the serious student says and how is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that going on within myself and how is\Nthat happening within myself
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.63,0:07:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so that brings us to understanding that\Nall truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:08:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,well no let's say all propositions\Ninvolve two things they involve content
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.31,0:08:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and they involve context.\NThe content is a literal statement
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.08,0:08:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone presumes a certain meaning\Nbut meaning comes out of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the gross distortions of the world\Nthat we see in everyday headlines
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.63,0:08:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do with the failure to\Nidentify
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.59,0:08:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,context.\NThe content is often verbatimly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,correct as far as most people's logic is\Nconcerned and reason
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.27,0:08:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,except within it it's only true within a\Ncertain context
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the failure is to identify context.\NThis is a fault of science
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.39,0:08:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nall areas of human endeavor. A thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:09:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,only true within a certain context in\Nand of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.76,0:09:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is the speaker or the\Neditorial writer,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.39,0:09:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the newspaper presumes that you will\Nassume a context
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.32,0:09:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is a great very great false\Nassumption that you will assume the same
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,context as they do because very often\Nthe context that you assume is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,completely different.\NUh, you know, it's always a joke when I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.80,0:09:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,see some bomber who has just killed 52\Npeople and blown up a plane and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.68,0:09:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,slaughtered all kinds of innocents and\Nthe minute he gets arrested, a parade
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,starts for his civil rights. You know,\Nyou say, "Yeah, right. What about the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.88,0:09:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,civil rights of the 3,000 people he's\Njust killed?" You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.48,0:09:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Npolitical rights um of course are what
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.95,0:10:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,historically Americans have died for.\NBut in this particular context it sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.32,0:10:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sophomoric and it actually ridicules the\Nbasic concept by misplacing it in in a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.56,0:10:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,context that almost invalidates its\Ntruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.20,0:10:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are only true then within a\Ncertain context and the unstated context
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.68,0:10:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is where the difficulty arises.\NAm I making sense to you this far? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.44,0:10:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All truth is only true within a certain\Ncontext. This is recognized in so-called
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.20,0:10:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,situational ethics\Nin which the ethic depends on the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.07,0:10:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances.\NEven courts uh give uh recognition to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.60,0:10:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that context\Nuh alters the degree of responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.04,0:10:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the insanity, the defense etc. Uh\Nwhether there's willfulness, intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nso the individual then is considered to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:11:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,be responsible only within a certain\Ncontext. So we can never presume
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,context. Context always has to be\Nexplicitly understood, stated or
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.44,0:11:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,made verbatim. Um\Nthe infinite context is what
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.20,0:11:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality is all about. Spirituality\Nis transcending content to realize the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.51,0:11:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,context out of which\Nall arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.51,0:11:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning of all these lectures,\NI think we we start out with a statement
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.20,0:11:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the ultimate infinite context\Nreally is of everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization that everything is\Nhappening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything we see is spontaneously being\Nwhat it is, exactly as it is this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.36,0:12:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,moment. And each moment is therefore\Nperfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.95,0:12:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For anything to be what it is at this\Nmoment, it has to fulfill
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.39,0:12:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nwhich is innate to its creation, innate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.88,0:12:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to its existence.\NSo that everything if the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.12,0:12:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,stopped this incident, everything is\Nperfect right now. Each thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.44,0:12:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming that which is innately its\Npotential.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.36,0:12:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see that the rose half unfolded is\Nnot an imperfect rose. It's perfect up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.07,0:12:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to this point. The perfect design is\Nthat this rose should unfold in this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.92,0:12:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,way. And at this moment it is the\Nabsolute perfection of that which has
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.63,0:12:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,gone before.\NAs you know that which has gone before
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is the totality of the entire universe\Nthroughout all of time. That's what it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.76,0:13:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,took for this rose to be right here at\Nthis moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.39,0:13:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the universe stops right now, it\Nhas already reached its perfection
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.27,0:13:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because its perfection is to be half\Nunfolded at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To see that that is the condition, the\Nstate of affairs
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.63,0:13:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is what hit me at Walmart yesterday.\NEverybody was just spontaneously being
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly who they were at the mo at that\Nmoment with no disguises, no, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.51,0:13:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,people dropped their persona in that\Nkind of a setting. So the lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's innate within the human condition\Nwas able to shine forth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that also after uh catastrophes\Nand all, you know, a shipwreck
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.27,0:13:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh comm camaraderie\Nand when the chips are down, everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.60,0:14:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly becomes who they really are.\NThen when they go back to work on Monday
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,morning, they're back to the same old\Nworld speak. You know, there's two kinds
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.12,0:14:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of speak. There's world speak and truth\Nspeak. And in world speak, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.44,0:14:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,expected to do to come across with world\Nspeak. And in truth speak is is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.48,0:14:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,inappropriate in world speak.\NIn world speak, you're supposed to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"No, I'm not guilty." Even though\Nthere's 21 bodies laying there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,21 kids you molested.\NNot guilty, your honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.36,0:14:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh that's real world speak. So we the\Ncontext we understand speak within a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,certain context. We understand that it's\Nworld speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.07,0:14:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophisticated people understand it's\Nworld speak. Most of the world doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.48,0:14:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the world thinks it's truth.\NWorld speak is a provisional
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.95,0:14:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,accommodation to\Num the practicalities of the everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.44,0:15:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,marketplace and physical survival\Nwithin ourselves. However, the condition
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of world speaking tends to continue.\Ninner voice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,uh continues to lie to ourself, create\Nillusions. And so today, what we want to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.83,0:15:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,do is try to transcend those illusions.\NOne way, the most important way, which
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we're speaking of today, that illusion\Narises is the failure to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.76,0:15:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,context.\NWhen we judge things, when we judge
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.00,0:15:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,things and when we judge oursel to\Nattack ourselves and others, the only
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.63,0:15:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,way you can do that is by removing it\Nfrom context.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you can attack yourself for\Nwhat you did yesterday or last year or
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.51,0:15:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,two years ago or whatever\Nis to forget the context in which it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.39,0:15:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,happened.\NSo Monday morning quarterbacking is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.24,0:16:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,always facious. Always facious. It's\Nalways felacious. Why? because it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.72,0:16:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,different context. Monday morning's\Ntruth is not the same as Saturday
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,afternoon's truth. They're two different\Ntruths.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.72,0:16:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The conditions which existed at the time\Nin the past are different than the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.27,0:16:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions which exist today.\NWhat was accepted worldwide as normal
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.48,0:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,human behavior\Ncan't be criticized now in retrospect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When I grew up, the woman's place was in\Nthe home. She ruled it like she the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.00,0:16:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,matriarch. The woman ruled the house and\Nthe man was supposed to go out there and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,bring home the bacon.\NHe didn't rule the house. He expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.83,0:16:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,his opinions. But uh if you like your\Nlike them diced better than slice, she
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,says dice is better for you diced, you\Nknow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.56,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So mother ruled in the house and she was\Nre revered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because she was the sustainer of life.\NYou know, the mother had a profound
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.40,0:17:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,importance. And as a boy, if you even if\Nyour mother asked you to whitewash the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.16,0:17:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,basement on a Saturday afternoon and you\Nhad to cancel your baseball game, if you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.07,0:17:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,looked even the slightest disappointed,\Nyour father would say, "Wipe that look
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.60,0:17:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,off your face, young boy." Young man,\Nit's disrespectful to your mother. Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the mother had high, you know,\Ntomorrow's mother's day that the mother
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.84,0:17:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,had a very high rank within her domain.\NShe uh rules supreme and men when she
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.76,0:17:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,entered the room stood up. You know that\Nlots of you in this world room I see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.08,0:17:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,from your age don't know what it means.\NWhen the woman entered the room the men
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all stood up. You see that today? No.\NWhen the woman under came up to the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:18:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,doorway, the man opened it for her. And\Nthose gestures were to honor her. You
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.88,0:18:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,understand? Women were being honored.\NThe women's movement didn't get that. It
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.79,0:18:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,was so paranoid. It didn't even get it\Nwas being honored. It thought it was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.91,0:18:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,being\Ninsulted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.24,0:18:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you. So anyway,\Nlow self-esteem and paranoia cease
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,insult everywhere. That that's the ego\Negotism of narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.16,0:18:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The entitled attitude and the narcissism\Nthat undermines so that you think that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,an to be honored is to be insulted. So\Nanyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.44,0:18:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother reigns supreme. You didn't\Nuse any vulgar language in in her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.76,0:18:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,presence. If you went to a tavern\Nrestaurant, there was a separate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,entrance in the rear was called family\Nentrance. Women never entered the front
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.91,0:18:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,entrance. That was for the bar and\Nvulgarity. And you never saw a single
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.24,0:19:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,woman at a bar. A woman walking up to a\Nbar. I never saw it in my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.44,0:19:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first time I did see it, I was\Nlike shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.96,0:19:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nall right. So, the woman's the woman's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,uh rank, her status, her worth was\Nrevered. revered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.08,0:19:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, the word mother was revered. The\Nmother
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.44,0:19:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was respected, revered and she was also\Nprotected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.32,0:19:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Men went to war to protect mother and\Nthe children. Her function was revered.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.72,0:19:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, and let's see what happened to that.\Nthe paranoid distortions that have
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.24,0:19:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,fallen uh fallen upon mother. Now\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.48,0:19:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see the context\Nmeans that when people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.67,0:19:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Monday morning quarterbacking\Nwould say woman had an inferior
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:20:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,position. Well this is from Monday\Nmorning's quarterbacking
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a perception that really misses\Nthe entire reality of what went on in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.36,0:20:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,those days. We can look back at slavery\Nand say, "Oh, how awful that was." Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.36,0:20:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's awful 250 years later when it's no\Nlonger a world style.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.88,0:20:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In the years in which slaver in the\Nyears of slavery, it's a world
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.03,0:20:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena.\NAll the countries of the world practice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.55,0:20:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,slavery.\NThe Arabic world still practices it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.79,0:20:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see by shifting context we can\Nlook at the role of you know they can
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.91,0:20:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,look back and say how wrong it was the\Nway women were held held down and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.00,0:20:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't get a job in the workplace.\NWell who wanted to I don't know a woman
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.15,0:20:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that wanted a job in the workplace.\NIt was thought when I grew up that to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.15,0:20:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have the woman in the house working was\Na disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:21:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,For a man to have his wife out there\Nworking was a disgrace. It means he
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't afford to make a living. His\Nwife had to go to work. It was pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody felt sorry for him. And he was\Na
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.00,0:21:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,uh he was a weak sister. You know, he\Ncan't make enough money to support his
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.67,0:21:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,wife. For God's sake, she she had to get\Na job at Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.24,0:21:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the meaning of a woman's working was\Ncompletely different. The only one woman
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.40,0:21:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who worked was the spinster who had to.\Nwhen everybody felt sorry for the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,dispenser.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.84,0:21:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see how different it's\Ncontextualized now. So you see what an
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,error it is to go into retrospect into a\Ndifferent context of relationship and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.55,0:21:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,humanity and what was normal and\Naccepted and expected. It was now
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.96,0:21:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,normal. It was expected everybody\Nfulfilled their social role
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.72,0:21:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as it was defined at the time.\NThere was no no. So you see now number
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.96,0:22:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of years later how we can make all that\Nwrong. We can go back 250 years and say
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.08,0:22:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how it was all wrong.\NWe can go back hundreds of years and say
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.64,0:22:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,how it was all wrong how the Irish were\Ntreated. The Irish were treated worse
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.08,0:22:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,than the blacks were treated.\NWe can say it was very wrong for the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.03,0:22:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,black kings of Africa\Nto capture
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,other people and sell them. Huh? So if\Nyou're looking for moral fault, you keep
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.88,0:22:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,going back farther and farther into the\Norigination. If there was slave trading,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.52,0:22:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,where did they get the slaves? They got\Nthem from slave traders. Where did the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.20,0:22:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,slave traders get them from? They got\Nthem from brokers on the docks. Where'
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.76,0:22:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the brokers on the docks got get them?\NThey were sold to them by the kings.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.20,0:22:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where' the kings get them? They got got\Nthem by intertribal warfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.00,0:22:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the lifestyle.\NInstead of killing the victims, they let
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.91,0:23:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,them live. But now they had to pay back\Nfor their life by a world by a life of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.24,0:23:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,service.\NSo from one context it was all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.03,0:23:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For another context, the social reality\Nof the time, you can't go back 300 years
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.28,0:23:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ago and say, you know, such and such was\Nwrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.76,0:23:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the olden days, there was over 500\Ndifferent offenses that were punishable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.76,0:23:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by death. The reign of King Louie the\Nsomething or other. I think there's five
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.88,0:23:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,500 offenses that you executed for.\NSo you see how felicia it is to shift
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.15,0:23:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,context\Nand go in retrospect and try to make
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.03,0:23:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong something that in the context of\Nthe time was not wrong. It was certainly
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.48,0:23:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not wrong for my mother to be honored\Nfor women to be honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.96,0:23:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't feel like I was putting women\Ndown to hold the door open for them. I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.40,0:24:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,still don't.\NSo, how can a woman feel insulted if I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.32,0:24:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hold the door open for them? I've had\Nthat happen. Open the carter and they
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.52,0:24:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Oh, I can open it myself." So, I\Nwas inclined by opening the door that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they were weak and I was superior, I\Nguess. See, so paranoia completely
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.36,0:24:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,distorts the reality. I was brought up\Nto honor women, stand up when they enter
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.48,0:24:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the room, hold the door open. So, I'm\Nhonoring them. And she thinks she's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.32,0:24:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,being dishonored. So, what a shift.\NDon't you see this? How context now
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.36,0:24:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,totally changes meaning. Context totally\Nchanges meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Shift context and you shift the\Nstatement to mean the opposite. To mean
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.67,0:24:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the opposite.\NTo mean the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.60,0:24:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is done all the time. This is done\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been done throughout history.\NIt's uh the Achilles heel of mankind is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.44,0:24:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can't recognize truth from\Nfalsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.52,0:25:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only real importance of the work\NI've done so far is to point out that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.76,0:25:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,nowadays there is a means by which\Nwe can discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.20,0:25:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout all of time, man has had no\Ncompass sailing the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.55,0:25:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult and dangerous seas of human\Nlife without even a compass to tell the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.15,0:25:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.\NSo it's almost like a new beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.40,0:25:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the work we're doing is is\Nunique in that I think it's for the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.27,0:25:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,first time in human history\Nthat we've been able to do legitimate,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.88,0:25:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,verifiable, bonafideed spiritual\Nresearch.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.79,0:25:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The only spiritual\Ninformation we've gotten has been the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.27,0:25:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneous inner awakening of various\Ngurus and sages and saints
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.79,0:25:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and beloved individuals in which it has\Nhappened spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.67,0:26:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or as the result of rigorous spiritual\Nwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.55,0:26:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have the information obtained by\Nthe subjective awareness of people who
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.48,0:26:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,become enlightened.\NAnd interestingly the subject subjective
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.36,0:26:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,state of\Nthe condition we call reality with a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.84,0:26:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,capital R has been the same for\Nthousands of years. There's no
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.79,0:26:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,variation.\NEvery individual who has reached a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.20,0:26:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,certain level of consciousness says\Nexactly the same thing. There's no
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.03,0:26:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,argument.\NNo argument. No difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.15,0:26:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps a different style of\Npresentation. Speech can be in Sanskrit
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.64,0:26:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or Latin.\NWhether it's in Sanskrit or Latin or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.88,0:26:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,English, the experience is the same.\NSo we have the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.44,0:27:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual truth has only been arrived at\Nas a profoundly subjective state
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.12,0:27:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore\Nthat's which I've stated in books and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.12,0:27:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,research\Nand in lectures is that the absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.20,0:27:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,reality is\Nradical subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.88,0:27:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to know anything about any\Nkind of truth is purely subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.32,0:27:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Purely subjective.\NThere's no way you can make an objective
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.24,0:27:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,statement.\NThere's no such thing as an objective
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.60,0:27:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,statement. An objective statement would\Nbe something that exists independent of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.24,0:27:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an observer. And in as much as it would\Nthere's no observer, there could be no
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.40,0:27:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,objective reality because there would be\Nno observer to make any remarks about
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.91,0:27:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NTherefore, the closest thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.55,0:27:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,science and the world has come to being\Nable to make such statements, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.52,0:28:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is revealed now by quantum mechanics\Nas subparticle physics of quantum
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.96,0:28:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanics in which\Nthe profound role of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.48,0:28:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is now demonstrated for all to see.\NAll of you familiar with quantum
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.48,0:28:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanics, raise your hand.\NAh, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.32,0:28:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know anything about it.\NSo, I'm glad you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.52,0:28:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We can just look at one simple fact for\Nthose who are not familiar with quantum
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.52,0:28:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanics. That as you get smaller and\Nsmaller particles, we discover that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.91,0:28:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there are no infinite small particles\Nthat constitute
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.24,0:28:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic subatoms of all things. That a\Nthing can exist as either a particle or
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.27,0:28:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a wave. and is problematic, which it\Nwill be.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.20,0:28:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And probably the most interesting\Nexperiment, which people who don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.20,0:29:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,anything about quantum mechanics find\Nquite fascinating, is that when you have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.76,0:29:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an atom of matter and it encounters an\Natom of antimatter,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.64,0:29:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they negate each other. And when that\Nhappens, two photons are shot shot off
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.52,0:29:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the space. Uh these photons uh do not\Nrotate.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.27,0:29:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh they go in opposite directions. this\Nside of the universe, this side of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.39,0:29:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,universe. But if an observer looks at\Nthis photon here, it begins to rotate.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.00,0:29:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very instant that he looks at\Nthis photon and it starts to rotate, the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.12,0:29:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,photon on the other side of the universe\Ninstantly starts to rotate in the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.72,0:29:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite direction. even though it's\Nunobserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.39,0:29:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The implication of all this then is that\Nthere is some matrix common to the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.64,0:29:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,entire universe which includes both\Nphotons within it. This photon does not
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.67,0:29:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,cause this photon to do anything\Nwhatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.36,0:30:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no contact with it\Nwithin the microscopic dimension of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.48,0:30:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian physics. It has no\Nrelationship with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.91,0:30:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That field which quantum mechanics comes\Nclosest to defining is what in spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.55,0:30:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,work we refer to as consciousness.\NWhen observed the photon begins to spin
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.55,0:30:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the photon on the opposite side of\Nthe universe begins to spin the opposite
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.60,0:30:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,direction just from the act of\Nobservation to merely look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.44,0:30:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the profound effect of\Nconsciousness.
